# Fluff Date: 2026-02-09 16:25:29
overview:161

capabilities:<p>The Avatar is a seventy-ton Inner Sphere OmniMech born from the Draconis Combine's ambitious effort to reverse-engineer Clan technology following the Battle of Luthien in 3052. Luthien Armor Works began development using captured Mad Dog OmniMechs as the basis for the design, making the Avatar the first Inner Sphere OmniMech conceptualized. Prolonged integration difficulties between Clan and Inner Sphere technologies, however, meant it was among the last of the Combine's first generation OmniMechs to enter production in 3056. Filling the role of a versatile heavy fire support platform, the Avatar leverages a generous thirty-four tons of pod space to accommodate a wide variety of weapon configurations. Licensed production through StarCorps Industries, Victory Industries, and General Motors has spread the design across multiple Successor States, establishing it as one of the most widely manufactured Inner Sphere OmniMechs in service.</p>

deployment:<p>The Avatar's chassis mounts a Hermes 280 XL engine, providing a top speed of sixty-four kilometers per hour. While notably slower than its Clan-designed ancestor, this trade-off in mobility purchases considerably more internal volume and pod capacity than the original Mad Dog offered. With thirty-four tons of available pod space, the Avatar can mount firepower rivaling many assault-weight designs while retaining the tactical flexibility inherent to OmniMech technology. Twelve tons of StarSlab/4 armor provide respectable protection for its weight class, supplemented by CASE systems in both side torsos to mitigate the catastrophic risk of ammunition detonation.</p><p>A distinctive feature of the design is its two permanently mounted Victory 23R medium lasers in the center torso. These hardwired weapons trace their origin to early testing phases when OmniPod connector faults risked leaving the entire weapons array disabled. Though the underlying issue was resolved before deployment, the fixed lasers remain as a design vestige ensuring the Avatar is never completely unarmed. In its Prime configuration, the Avatar combines an LB 10-X autocannon with dual LRM-10 launchers equipped with Artemis IV fire control, supplemented by medium pulse lasers and machine guns for a balanced loadout emphasizing ranged engagement with credible close-in capability.</p>

history:<p>The Alternate Configuration A transforms the Avatar into a dedicated close-combat brawler. An ER large laser provides its sole long-range capability, while an Autocannon/20 and paired SRM-6 launchers deliver devastating short-range firepower. Four jump jets grant the normally ground-bound chassis unexpected mobility, allowing MechWarriors to exploit terrain and close rapidly with targets. This combination of jump capability and overwhelming close-range punch makes the A configuration particularly effective as an anti-Elemental platform and urban warfare combatant.</p>

primaryfactory:Luthien Armor Works, StarCorps Industries, StarCorps Industries, StarCorps Industries, StarCorps Industries, Victory Industries (formerly Norse BattleMech Works), General Motors/Blackwell Corporation

